<font color="#FF0000">POLITICS</font><br>
<tt>Mon Nov  3  1:50:24 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I think of all of the tragedy that politics gave us in Vietnam.  My father was a lifer, I didn't want to go, but was drafted when I was 27.  I have looked upon all of this as the years have gone by and cried at all of the waste.  The lives, the young children of our country.  Thrown away because of politicians<br><br>
I think today of all of the tragedy that politics give to us in America as we teach.  (I became a special education teacher courtesy of my GI bill only 6 years ago)  I again see the lives of the young children of our country being thrown away because of politicians.  In the inner city the young children, predominately black, are being denied the benefits of a first class education because of politics again.  Will we never learn?  We know how to teach, we know how to rectify the problems.  Many years ago we knew what was right and how to win a war but we were never allowed to.  History repeats itself.  But now we are even closer to home.  <br><br>
I cried at all of the young lives wasted.  Today I still cry at all of the young lives wasted.  Back then I couldn't see the dead because they were so far away.  Today I touch the living and know they are already dead, doomed by politics of our education system.  <br><br>
When will we ever learn?
<p><code>-- trasmus@aol.com  (Tony Rasmus III) </code><p>


